ZCZC EE54
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 162300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES ACROSS
THE ENGLISH CHANNEL WHILE LARGE DEEP LOW LIES CENTRED
964 W OF SOLE BRINGING STRG WINDS TO ALL AREAS EXCEPT
THE ENGLISH CHANNEL AND GALES POSS IN FITZROY SOLE AND
SHANNON. OVERNIGHT FRIDAY AND DURING SATURDAY THE LOW
MOVS N AND E CENTRED 965 BAILEY BY SATURDAY EVENING
WITH STRG WINDS SPREADING TO ALL AREAS BUT GALES EASING
IN FITZROY SOLE AND SHANNON. OVERNIGHT SATURDAY AND
DURING SUNDAY THE LOW CONTINUES TO MOV NE AND BEGINS TO
FILL CENTRED 968 N OF THE FAEROES BY SUNDAY EVENING
WITH A SW FLOW BECMG ESTABLISHED ACROSS ALL AREAS. STRG
WINDS GRADUALLY EASE ACROSS ALL OF NITON. OVERNIGHT
SUNDAY AND DURING MONDAY THE SW FLOW STRENGTHENS AGAIN AS
HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS OVER EUROPE WITH STRG WINDS
DEVELOPING IN ALL AREAS AND GALES POSS IN LUNDY FASTNET
IRISH SEA AND SHANNON
